Ramadan considerations, post-Eid hiring surges, year-end planning).Coordinate with leadership to translate product updates and client outcomes into social-ready content. Content Creation &amp; ProductionWrite strong, conversion-friendly copy (especially for LinkedIn), with a clear understanding of hooks, storytelling, and CTAs.Design or coordinate visuals (carousel posts, short motion graphics, simple branded templates).Create short-form video content (script + structure; filming/editing is a plus but not mandatory if you can manage freelancers).Repurpose content across formats: turn a blog into 6 LinkedIn posts, a webinar into clips, testimonials into carousels, and FAQs into short videos. Community, Engagement &amp; Brand VoiceManage daily engagement: respond to comments, DMs, and mentions quickly and professionally.Proactively engage with relevant communities: recruiters, staffing founders, HR managers, and business pages across KSA/UAE.Build relationships with creators and micro-influencers in recruitment, HR, and career content.Maintain a consistent tone: professional, direct, helpful, and confident—never spammy. Campaigns &amp; GrowthPlan and execute campaigns for lead magnets, webinars, product launches, hiring drives, and brand partnerships.Collaborate with sales to create social assets that support outreach (e.g., “why Recruitlytics” posts, objection-handling posts, credibility posts).Work with performance marketing (if applicable) to turn top organic content into paid campaigns. Analytics &amp; OptimizationTrack and report weekly/monthly performance: reach, engagement, follower growth, clicks, lead volume, and conversion metrics.Run experiments: hooks, formats, posting times, CTA tests, and content pillars.Build a “what works” library and refine strategy based on results.What Success Looks Like (KPIs)Consistent publishing cadence with high-quality content across priority platforms.Month-over-month growth in reach, engagement rate, and follower count.Increased inbound interest: demo requests, website clicks, WhatsApp/DM inquiries (if used), and lead magnet downloads.Strong community sentiment: meaningful comments, shares, saves, and recruiter/HR conversations.A clearly recognizable Recruitlytics voice and visual identity.Requirements2+ years of social media management experience (B2B SaaS, recruiting, staffing, HR tech, or business services is a plus).Strong writing skills in English (Arabic is a major advantage but not required; Arabic copywriting ability is a plus).Experience building content calendars and executing consistently.Comfortable with tools like Canva, CapCut (or similar), Google Workspace, and social scheduling platforms (Buffer, Hootsuite, Later, etc.).Strong understanding of LinkedIn content performance (hooks, carousels, thought leadership, storytelling, value posts).Ability to work independently, manage deadlines, and coordinate feedback cycles.Nice-to-Have SkillsShort-form video editing and on-camera confidence (or ability to direct others).Basic design sense and ability to keep brand consistency.Knowledge of recruitment workflows: sourcing, outreach, ATS, screening, hiring funnels.Experience supporting founders/executives with personal branding on LinkedIn.Working Style &amp; Time ZoneRemote role with availability overlapping Saudi/UAE business hours (flexible, but responsiveness matters).You’ll collaborate with marketing and leadership through Slack/WhatsApp/Zoom and track work through shared boards/docs.Why Join RecruitlyticsBuild a brand with real impact in a fast-growing market (KSA/UAE hiring).High ownership: you lead the social strategy and can shape what we become known for.Performance-driven environment where your work is visible and measurable.Opportunity to grow into Head of Social / Content Lead as we scale."}
